p.span: In its efforts to promote nondiscrimination and as required by law, Cayuga ISD does not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sex, disability, age, or any other basis prohibited by law, in providing education services, activities, and programs, including CTE programs, and provides equal access to the Boy Scouts and other designated youth groups. The following district representatives have been designated to coordinate compliance with these legal requirements:

● Title IX Coordinator, for concerns regarding discrimination on the basis of sex, including sexual harassment or gender-based harassment: Nancy Griffey, MS/HS Counselor, Address: Hwy 287 N Cayuga, TX 75832 903-2965.
● ADA/Section 504 Coordinator, for concerns regarding discrimination on the basis of disability: Nancy Griffey, MS/HS Counselor, Address: Hwy 287 N Cayuga, TX 75832 903-928-2965.
● All other concerns regarding discrimination: See the superintendent, Dr. Rick Webb, 903-928-2102; email - rwebb@cayugaisd.com [See policies FB, FFH, and GKD.]
